Description:
General Summary
Provides technical expertise, support, and functional management for spatially enabled databases and server based Geographic Information Systems (GIS). Performs technical administration, installation, configuration, maintenance, update, and optimization of GIS infrastructure. Provides quality assurance and manages GIS infrastructure content and security. Participates in the long-term development and enhancement of GIS information technology to meet GIS Team and Information Technology Department goals.
Essential Functions
Collaborates and works closely with GIS and IT personnel to provide enterprise level geospatial solutions;
Works with GIS staff to administer, secure, publish, and update ArcGIS Enterprise and ArcGIS Online content;
Installs, configures, and maintains server-based GIS software;
Designs, optimizes, and maintains spatially enabled databases;
Manages ArcGIS Portal site design and administration;
Provides training and technical advice to users;
Provides input into long-term county GIS strategies;
Develops project plans and coordinates with management to implement GIS infrastructure projects;
Works with IT staff to troubleshoot and resolve GIS related hardware and software issues;
Conducts advanced research into emerging technologies and works with vendors, consultants and other resources to determine capability of products;
Evaluates, advises, and implements quality control standards and maintenance procedures for geographic information system databases and infrastructure.

ADDITIONAL FUNCTIONS

Assists with security and data access-related procedures;
Performs related functions as required.
Job Requirements
Bachelor’s degree from an accredited university in GIS, Information Technology, Computer Science or a related field and minimum of 4 years’ experience managing spatial data and geospatial content; OR an equivalent combination of education and experience;
CompTIA Certification preferred;
Advanced knowledge of GIS infrastructure administration and support;
Advanced knowledge of spatial data management;
Advanced knowledge of ArcGIS Enterprise and ArcGIS Online content administration and user management;
Advanced knowledge of ArcSDE and SQL Server based spatial data technologies;
Knowledge and understanding of SAML single sign-on and production/test environment best practices;
Knowledge and understanding of web-based technologies including high availability architecture, Javascript, HTML, CSS, and REST framework;
Knowledge and understanding of scripting principles, specifically Python;
Ability to communicate complex technical information in an understandable, non-technical fashion;
Ability to work productively both independently and as part of a team;
Ability to follow written and verbal instructions and present ideas logically and effectively;
Ability to maintain effective working relationships.

OTHER REQUIREMENTS

Must possess and maintain a valid driver’s license.
Work Environment & Physical Demands
Work is performed primarily in an office environment and the employee in this class is subject to inside environmental conditions;
May be required to lift up to 20 lbs.;
Requires frequent repetitive movement of the wrists, hands, and fingers.

DISCLAIMER:
To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform the essential functions satisfactorily with or without reasonable accommodation. The above statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being assigned to this job. They are not intended to be construed as an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties and skills required of individuals in the job. This job description is not an employment agreement and/or an expressed or implied employment contract. Management has the exclusive right to alter this job description at any time without notice. Ada County provides Veteran's Preference for all County jobs except for those deemed "key positions" in accordance with Title 65, Chapter 5 of Idaho Code.

